<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-06T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="141" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">548.D1/292: Telegram (part air)</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-06T14:00:00-05:00">April 6, 1936—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>27. Despatch No. 4301 from Berne concerning Inter-Governmental Conference
                            on status of refugees.</p>
                        <p>This Government does not contemplate participating actively in that
                            Conference but desires that you, or in your absence a member of your
                            staff, attend as an observer. If you have any comment or suggestion to
                            make regarding this assignment please telegraph at once.</p>
                        <p>Background material for your information will be transmitted by mail.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>